  "lesson": {
    "title": "RC Smoothing Circuit",
    "description": "Tap the tact button quickly. USB → button → 470Ω → split: 1000µF cap (center) and red LED (east) in parallel. The capacitor stores charge between taps and smooths the pulses — the LED stays lit or dims gradually instead of snapping off like lesson 8. Compare lesson 23 (4.7kΩ slows one long press) and lesson 29 (pot + small cap filters wiggles). τ ≈ 0.5 s; cap + toward power; LED east at 90°."
  },
